Key Match Events: Trae Young hit a half-court 3-pointer at the buzzer to give the Atlanta Hawks a 124-121 win over the Utah Jazz.
Collin Sexton tied the game with four seconds left on a 24-foot trey.
Trae Young finished with 24 points and 20 assists.
Clint Capela contributed 18 points, six rebounds, and three blocks.
Lauri Markkanen led Utah with 35 points.
Walker Kessler had 21 points, 10 rebounds, and three blocks.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Hawks played without second-leading scorer Jalen Johnson due to right shoulder inflammation.
The Jazz were without former Hawks forward John Collins, Keyonte George, and Brice Sensabaugh due to various reasons.
